1
00:00:07,707 --> 00:00:09,174
- Earth.

2
00:00:09,176 --> 00:00:10,843
Fire.

3
00:00:10,845 --> 00:00:12,411
Air.

4
00:00:12,413 --> 00:00:13,345
Water.

5
00:00:13,347 --> 00:00:18,250
Only the avatar can master
all four elements

6
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:22,121
and bring balance
to the world.

7
00:00:26,493 --> 00:00:27,259
- Someone has attacked

8
00:00:27,261 --> 00:00:28,827
the Southern water tribe
cultural center.

9
00:00:28,829 --> 00:00:31,497
All the evidence points
to northern sympathizers,

10
00:00:31,499 --> 00:00:34,433
but mako suspects
there's more to this case.

11
00:00:34,435 --> 00:00:36,335
Meanwhile,
varrick has cast bolin

12
00:00:36,337 --> 00:00:37,936
as the hero
of his newest mover.

13
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:40,773
Asami has also ventured
into business with varrick,

14
00:00:40,775 --> 00:00:43,242
and a shipment
of her mecha-tanks is on its way

15
00:00:43,244 --> 00:00:47,079
to help the South
in its war against unalaq.

16
00:00:59,993 --> 00:01:02,861
[Beeping]

17
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:09,301
[Beeping]

18
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:13,806
- We're under attack!

19
00:01:22,482 --> 00:01:26,952
Varrick is not gonna
be happy about this.

20
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:34,093
[Wind whistling]

21
00:01:43,236 --> 00:01:44,603
- Where is he?

22
00:01:44,605 --> 00:01:47,806
- Father said he would
meet us at this location.

23
00:01:47,808 --> 00:01:52,111
He'll be here.

24
00:01:55,982 --> 00:01:58,584
Were you just
in the spirit world?

25
00:01:58,586 --> 00:02:01,920
- Never mind that.
Where is the avatar?

26
00:02:01,922 --> 00:02:03,689
- She was within our grasp

27
00:02:03,691 --> 00:02:06,391
until a dark spirit
attacked her.

28
00:02:06,393 --> 00:02:08,360
- They're out of control.

29
00:02:08,362 --> 00:02:10,562
- You didn't get her?

30
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:13,599
- The avatar is dead.

31
00:02:16,202 --> 00:02:19,805
[Exciting music]

32
00:02:19,807 --> 00:02:27,446
♪

33
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:32,084
- We finally made it.

34
00:02:32,086 --> 00:02:35,020
Now we must stop
the evil unalaq!

35
00:02:35,022 --> 00:02:38,056
[Crowd cheering]

36
00:02:38,058 --> 00:02:41,760
- The Southern water tribe
is mine.

37
00:02:41,762 --> 00:02:44,229
Next, I will conquer
the world

38
00:02:44,231 --> 00:02:48,000
with my waterbending
doomsday device!

39
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:53,472
[Crowd jeering]

40
00:02:53,474 --> 00:02:55,274
- Don't worry,
juji and roh-tan,

41
00:02:55,276 --> 00:02:57,943
I will end the evil unalaq's
reign of terror.

42
00:02:57,945 --> 00:03:01,146
For I am nuktuk,
hero of the South!

43
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:03,148
[Crowd cheers]

44
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:07,519
- Nuktuk, you're not just
the hero of the South,

45
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:09,988
you're our best friend.

46
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:10,822
Nuktuk-ity!

47
00:03:10,824 --> 00:03:14,159
- You two are the best
snow raccoon and arctic panda

48
00:03:14,161 --> 00:03:16,328
a guy could ask for.

49
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:17,029
All: Aww.

50
00:03:17,031 --> 00:03:19,965
- ♪ Who's gonna fight
for friends and freedom? ♪

51
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:20,566
♪ nuktuk

52
00:03:20,568 --> 00:03:22,601
♪ he's the biggest, baddest ♪

53
00:03:22,603 --> 00:03:24,970
♪ bendingest man I know

54
00:03:24,972 --> 00:03:27,906
♪ who protects the icy tundra?
Nuktuk ♪

55
00:03:27,908 --> 00:03:31,510
♪ battling northies
out there in the snow ♪

56
00:03:31,512 --> 00:03:33,445
♪ when unalaq starts trouble

57
00:03:33,447 --> 00:03:35,681
♪ he'll punch him
in the mouth ♪

58
00:03:35,683 --> 00:03:39,451
♪ he's nuktuk,
the hero of the South ♪

59
00:03:39,453 --> 00:03:44,556
[Cheering]

60
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:47,559
- Bolin, look up there.
What do you see?

61
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:48,894
- I--
is this a trick question?

62
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:51,797
- I'll tell you what I see--
a star being born.

63
00:03:51,799 --> 00:03:53,665
You're a star.
People love stars.

64
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:56,768
Stars tell them what to think
and how to act.

65
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,470
Bolin, have you ever
tried to force

66
00:03:58,472 --> 00:04:00,272
a monkey-marmot
to ride a bicycle?

67
00:04:00,274 --> 00:04:03,342
- Uh...Not that I can recall.

68
00:04:03,344 --> 00:04:04,142
- Of course you haven't.

69
00:04:04,144 --> 00:04:06,612
You can't force monkey-marmots
to do anything.

70
00:04:06,614 --> 00:04:10,349
They've got to want
to do it themselves.

71
00:04:10,351 --> 00:04:12,217
- Right.
- With these movers,

72
00:04:12,219 --> 00:04:13,719
we'll have the support
of the people,

73
00:04:13,721 --> 00:04:15,988
and before long,
they'll persuade the president

74
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:19,458
to lend his troops
to the war effort.

75
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:24,763
- [Sinister laugh]

76
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,465
My evil plan is working.

77
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:30,902
I've captured
nuktuk's beautiful girlfriend.

78
00:04:30,904 --> 00:04:33,338
- Not so fast,
evil unalaq!

79
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:39,211
Oh, I will save
my true love and the South!

80
00:04:39,213 --> 00:04:43,081
[Heroic music]

81
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:43,949
Both: Unh!

82
00:04:43,951 --> 00:04:46,818
- And now,
your time is up.

83
00:04:48,821 --> 00:04:51,523
[Dramatic music]

84
00:04:51,525 --> 00:04:55,661
[Men grunting]

85
00:04:58,064 --> 00:04:59,998
- It's no use fighting,
nuktuk.

86
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:04,636
My anti-energy net
makes bending impossible.

87
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:05,837
[Sinister laugh]

88
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:08,307
- No! Please.

89
00:05:08,309 --> 00:05:11,743
Power...Weakening.

90
00:05:11,745 --> 00:05:12,944
- Nuk-terrible.

91
00:05:12,946 --> 00:05:15,180
- Will this be the end
of nuktuk?

92
00:05:15,182 --> 00:05:17,516
Can he escape
from unalaq's trap

93
00:05:17,518 --> 00:05:18,784
and save the beautiful ginger?

94
00:05:18,786 --> 00:05:22,721
Find out next week
on the <i>adventures of nuktuk:</i>

95
00:05:22,723 --> 00:05:24,456
<i>Hero of the South.</i>

96
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:25,357
[Cheers and applause]

97
00:05:25,359 --> 00:05:30,062
- Wow. We got
some major chemistry on-screen.

98
00:05:30,064 --> 00:05:33,765
Am I right?
- Yeah. <i>On-screen.</i>

99
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:34,866
[Scoffs]
- What's wrong?

100
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:37,202
Are you mad because I left you
in the clutches

101
00:05:37,204 --> 00:05:38,003
of the evil unalaq?

102
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:39,805
I'm gonna save you
in the next episode.

103
00:05:39,807 --> 00:05:41,840
Ginger,
let's work through this.

104
00:05:41,842 --> 00:05:45,010
- Varrick, another one
of your ships has been captured.

105
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:46,945
- Darn it, zhu li,
haven't I told you

106
00:05:46,947 --> 00:05:50,382
I hate getting bad news
without first getting good news?

107
00:05:50,384 --> 00:05:51,850
- Oh, well,
the good news is

108
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:54,986
it looks like your first mover
has gotten a great reception.

109
00:05:54,988 --> 00:05:58,824
- That's old news!
Let's go.

110
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,331
[Door opens]

111
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:08,300
- Is it true?

112
00:06:08,302 --> 00:06:11,536
- I'm so sorry.
Your entire shipment was stolen.

113
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:14,406
- Without that sale,
I don't know how much longer

114
00:06:14,408 --> 00:06:16,174
I can keep my company going.

115
00:06:16,176 --> 00:06:17,442
What am I gonna do?

116
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:18,377
- Don't worry.

117
00:06:18,379 --> 00:06:20,746
I'm gonna find
whoever's responsible.

118
00:06:20,748 --> 00:06:22,748
Chief beifong
is about to question

119
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,249
the captain of the ship.

120
00:06:24,251 --> 00:06:25,283
[Feedback hum]

121
00:06:25,285 --> 00:06:26,685
- I know
it's been a long day,

122
00:06:26,687 --> 00:06:28,053
but walk me
through what happened.

123
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:31,790
- We were ambushed about
30 klicks outside the harbor.

124
00:06:31,792 --> 00:06:32,858
We never heard them coming.

125
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,793
- This is the third attack
this week.

126
00:06:34,795 --> 00:06:35,894
At about the same location.

127
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:40,265
- Yep, and smack-dab
in Republic city's jurisdiction,

128
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:42,200
which means
another problem for us.

129
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:46,238
All this stress is gonna
turn old black beauty gray.

130
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,106
- It's gotta be
northern water tribe.

131
00:06:48,108 --> 00:06:50,876
They're trying to stop
supply lines to the South.

132
00:06:50,878 --> 00:06:53,078
- I agree.
Is there anything else

133
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,846
about the attack you remember?

134
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:56,548
Anything unusual?

135
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:57,449
- There is one thing.

136
00:06:57,451 --> 00:07:00,952
The bombs exploded in a way
I've never seen before.

137
00:07:00,954 --> 00:07:01,920
They didn't have fuses.

138
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:04,790
It was like they were
being detonated remotely.

139
00:07:04,792 --> 00:07:07,492
- Like the bombs
at the cultural center.

140
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:09,094
- Wait,
where are you going?

141
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:12,898
- I gotta grab
some evidence.

142
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:13,665
- Asami, I heard the news.

143
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:16,334
I can't believe they took
my fifth favorite ship

144
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:18,804
in the varrick industries
fleet!

145
00:07:18,806 --> 00:07:20,338
Named her after my mom.

146
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:22,007
Rest in peace,
rocky bottom.

147
00:07:22,009 --> 00:07:24,242
- Without the money
from that shipment,

148
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:25,911
future industries is
almost broke.

149
00:07:25,913 --> 00:07:28,613
- Chief, I think there's
a link between this attack

150
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:30,282
and the attack
at the cultural center.

151
00:07:30,284 --> 00:07:31,983
- What do you think
you're doing?

152
00:07:31,985 --> 00:07:34,152
- Solving this case.

153
00:07:34,154 --> 00:07:35,520
Did any of the people
who attacked you

154
00:07:35,522 --> 00:07:37,022
have one of these
in their hand?

155
00:07:37,024 --> 00:07:40,292
I think
it's a remote detonator.

156
00:07:40,294 --> 00:07:43,495
- It was too dark
to see anything.

157
00:07:43,497 --> 00:07:43,895
- Mako!

158
00:07:43,897 --> 00:07:46,131
- Chief, I don't think
the people who attacked

159
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:47,065
were northern water tribe.

160
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:50,235
- Of course they were
northern water tribe.

161
00:07:50,237 --> 00:07:51,736
They were waterbending.

162
00:07:51,738 --> 00:07:55,240
- Was this one of the guys
who attacked?

163
00:07:55,242 --> 00:07:57,142
- No, I don't recognize him.

164
00:07:57,144 --> 00:07:59,177
- Oh, that's embarrassing.

165
00:07:59,179 --> 00:08:01,746
- [Chuckles]
Nice try, rookie.

166
00:08:01,748 --> 00:08:05,083
- Mako, leave.
Now.

167
00:08:05,085 --> 00:08:06,017
- Great work, everybody.

168
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:09,921
Another open and shut case
for the dynamic mustachioed duo!

169
00:08:09,923 --> 00:08:12,624
- Wait, I think mako
might be onto something.

170
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:14,526
- Chief, I know
it's a long shot,

171
00:08:14,528 --> 00:08:17,095
but I have an idea
how we can catch these guys.

172
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:19,698
- Yeah, let's all listen
to the rookie.

173
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,766
- He's doing a better job
than you.

174
00:08:21,768 --> 00:08:23,368
- Who's hungry?

175
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:24,636
- Enough!
- [Clears throat]

176
00:08:24,638 --> 00:08:27,372
- I don't want to hear
your lame-brained rookie ideas.

177
00:08:27,374 --> 00:08:29,574
You're a beat cop,
not a detective.

178
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:31,743
Now hit the street
and do your job!

179
00:08:31,745 --> 00:08:33,945
[Both laughing]

180
00:08:33,947 --> 00:08:35,680
- Lu and gang are idiots.

181
00:08:35,682 --> 00:08:38,049
I hate them
and their stupid mustaches.

182
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:41,286
- Forget them.
What's this idea of yours?

183
00:08:41,288 --> 00:08:42,454
- A sting operation.

184
00:08:42,456 --> 00:08:44,589
I was thinking
we'd set up a bait ship,

185
00:08:44,591 --> 00:08:45,924
take it out
into the open ocean,

186
00:08:45,926 --> 00:08:47,692
and capture
whoever attacks it.

187
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:48,560
- Let's do it.

188
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:49,327
- It's not that easy.

189
00:08:49,329 --> 00:08:51,530
For the plan to work,
we need the police,

190
00:08:51,532 --> 00:08:52,631
and beifong already
said no.

191
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:56,001
- We can make it work,
just the two of us.

192
00:08:56,003 --> 00:08:56,601
- I don't know.

193
00:08:56,603 --> 00:08:58,570
I don't want to go
behind beifong's back.

194
00:08:58,572 --> 00:09:02,073
If she finds out, I could get
kicked off the force.

195
00:09:02,075 --> 00:09:04,242
- Mako, I need your help.

196
00:09:04,244 --> 00:09:06,811
My mom is gone.
My dad is in jail.

197
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:10,348
Future industries is all
I have left of my family.

198
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:12,417
- I want to help you,

199
00:09:12,419 --> 00:09:15,520
but this is more
than a two-person job.

200
00:09:15,522 --> 00:09:17,756
First of all,
we'd need a ship.

201
00:09:17,758 --> 00:09:18,256
Both: Aah!

202
00:09:18,258 --> 00:09:19,591
- You need a ship?
I got a ship.

203
00:09:19,593 --> 00:09:22,160
I want in on
whatever you're talking about.

204
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:23,595
I love being in
on plans.

205
00:09:23,597 --> 00:09:25,030
- The less you know,
the better.

206
00:09:25,032 --> 00:09:27,065
- Perfect!
I love not knowing things.

207
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:31,369
- All right, I'm in.
Let's get these guys.

208
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,809
[Sea gulls squawking]

209
00:09:38,778 --> 00:09:41,546
[Metal doors squeak]

210
00:09:43,749 --> 00:09:46,217
- The ship's all loaded
with the dummy crates.

211
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:48,320
Let's get
this sting operation going.

212
00:09:48,322 --> 00:09:51,590
- Not yet.
We need some extra manpower.

213
00:09:51,592 --> 00:09:53,058
- What about korra?

214
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:54,859
No better muscle
than the avatar.

215
00:09:54,861 --> 00:09:57,028
- Right, uh...Korra.

216
00:09:57,030 --> 00:10:00,298
Yeah, actually, she's, um--
she's out of town right now.

217
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,133
- Everything okay
with you two?

218
00:10:02,135 --> 00:10:04,302
- Yeah, yeah.
Forget about korra.

219
00:10:04,304 --> 00:10:06,404
I'll go talk to bolin.

220
00:10:06,406 --> 00:10:09,207
[Old-timey jazz music]

221
00:10:09,209 --> 00:10:10,308
♪

222
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:12,477
- Hey, mako,
what do you think?

223
00:10:12,479 --> 00:10:13,578
I did
a little redecorating.

224
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:16,181
It turns out that one
of the perks of being a star--

225
00:10:16,183 --> 00:10:17,248
you get lots of cash.

226
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:20,352
- Is this a marble statue
of you?

227
00:10:20,354 --> 00:10:23,121
- It's also a hat rack.

228
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,723
- We don't even have hats.

229
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:28,326
- That's because
we've never had a hat rack.

230
00:10:28,328 --> 00:10:31,496
And now we do.
Mako, you seem stressed.

231
00:10:31,498 --> 00:10:34,833
I think you need to take
a little dipity dip.

232
00:10:34,835 --> 00:10:36,901
- I don't have time to take
a dipity dip, okay?

233
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:39,270
I'm trying to catch whoever's
been attacking the shipments,

234
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:41,373
and I need your help.
- You need my help?

235
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:45,343
[Groans] I don't know.
I'm kinda busy.

236
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:47,078
- You're sitting
in a hot tub.

237
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,414
- I'm maintaining
my instrument.

238
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:53,752
As an actor,
my body is my instrument.

239
00:10:53,754 --> 00:10:54,819
- Are you gonna help or not?

240
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,521
- You know,
I recall a time

241
00:10:56,523 --> 00:10:57,555
when I needed your help,

242
00:10:57,557 --> 00:10:59,691
and you basically told me
to get a life.

243
00:10:59,693 --> 00:11:00,792
- So that's a no.

244
00:11:00,794 --> 00:11:02,460
What am I supposed
to do now?

245
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:03,828
- I don't know, mako.

246
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,196
Figure it out.
Remember?

247
00:11:05,198 --> 00:11:10,001
That's what you said to me.
Hurts, doesn't it?

248
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:13,138
- [Grunts]
- [Screams]

249
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:16,274
Ow! My instrument!

250
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:18,143
[Dog barks in distance]

251
00:11:18,145 --> 00:11:20,712
- Are you sure
this is a good idea?

252
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:24,282
- No, but it's
our last resort.

253
00:11:28,054 --> 00:11:29,287
- Hey, mako.

254
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:32,190
Whatever you think we did,
we didn't do it.

255
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:34,059
- I'm not here
on police business.

256
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:36,594
I'm running
an off-the-books operation,

257
00:11:36,596 --> 00:11:37,996
and I thought
the triple threats

258
00:11:37,998 --> 00:11:40,498
might want a piece
of the action.

259
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,767
- How big a piece?

260
00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:50,108
- So Mr. law and order
needs our help, huh?

261
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:52,544
What's in it
for the triple threats?

262
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:55,213
- I am personal friends
with the avatar.

263
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,681
I might be able
to convince her

264
00:11:56,683 --> 00:11:58,983
to give shady shin
his bending back.

265
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:02,454
- Sounds good to me, boss.

266
00:12:02,456 --> 00:12:04,656
- What about the rest
of us?

267
00:12:04,658 --> 00:12:05,557
- I've got vehicles,

268
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:08,326
all brand-new
and top of the line.

269
00:12:08,328 --> 00:12:09,928
They can be yours
if you help.

270
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:16,468
- I think we got ourselves
a deal.

271
00:12:22,608 --> 00:12:25,076
- This is right around the area
where the attacks happened.

272
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,345
So keep your eyes peeled,
and stay quiet.

273
00:12:27,347 --> 00:12:30,448
- I agree. Keep quiet,
mouth zipped, don't say a word.

274
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:31,316
That's the best thing to do

275
00:12:31,318 --> 00:12:32,584
when you're trying
to ambush somebody,

276
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:33,785
which is what
we're doing here,

277
00:12:33,787 --> 00:12:35,720
and it's basically
what I'm always doing.

278
00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:37,655
I mean, I am a gangster,
after all, and--

279
00:12:37,657 --> 00:12:40,225
- two toed ping, please.

280
00:12:40,227 --> 00:12:41,326
- Oh, right.

281
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:44,596
So what's it like
dating the avatar?

282
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:45,230
- [Sighs]

283
00:12:45,232 --> 00:12:47,999
- Come on, mako,
I gotta know.

284
00:12:48,001 --> 00:12:49,501
- Ping, stay focused!

285
00:12:49,503 --> 00:12:51,736
- What?
Why are you so weird about it?

286
00:12:51,738 --> 00:12:54,773
If I was dating the avatar,
I'd tell you all about it.

287
00:12:54,775 --> 00:12:58,109
- There's nothing to know.

288
00:12:58,111 --> 00:12:59,744
I broke up with her.

289
00:12:59,746 --> 00:13:01,546
- You broke up?

290
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:04,282
When?
Why didn't you tell me?

291
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:05,283
- I don't know.

292
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:08,119
- [Laughs]
Yeah, right.

293
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:10,588
<i>You</i> broke up
with the avatar.

294
00:13:10,590 --> 00:13:12,056
Like that happened.

295
00:13:12,058 --> 00:13:14,726
Hey, shady shin, viper.

296
00:13:14,728 --> 00:13:17,796
Mako says he broke up
with the avatar.

297
00:13:17,798 --> 00:13:21,232
- Sure he did.
- Yeah, I did too.

298
00:13:21,234 --> 00:13:22,634
[Laughter]

299
00:13:22,636 --> 00:13:26,905
- All right, would you guys
knock it off and do your job?

300
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:34,078
- And action!

301
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,047
- Forget about me.

302
00:13:36,049 --> 00:13:38,583
You must capture
the evil unalaq

303
00:13:38,585 --> 00:13:39,818
before he gets away.

304
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:43,822
- No!
I'll never leave you.

305
00:13:43,824 --> 00:13:45,490
- Mm!

306
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:46,057
- Cut!

307
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:47,759
There's no kiss
in the script.

308
00:13:47,761 --> 00:13:50,829
- Sorry, I just kinda
lost myself in the moment.

309
00:13:50,831 --> 00:13:53,097
It just felt so right.
- Ugh!

310
00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:55,667
- It did, huh?
Your girlfriend's about to die,

311
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:59,504
and instead of untying her,
you kiss her.

312
00:13:59,506 --> 00:14:00,438
Wait a minute!

313
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,040
Maybe that will work.

314
00:14:02,042 --> 00:14:03,808
Yes! It's genius!

315
00:14:03,810 --> 00:14:04,843
Everybody take five.

316
00:14:04,845 --> 00:14:07,212
Except for you, zhu li.
Grab the tweezers.

317
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:10,515
I've got some neck-hair issues
to resolve.

318
00:14:10,517 --> 00:14:11,716
[Bell rings]

319
00:14:11,718 --> 00:14:15,353
- So...That kiss.
I liked it.

320
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:18,990
And it seemed like
you liked it too.

321
00:14:18,992 --> 00:14:19,824
- Ugh!

322
00:14:19,826 --> 00:14:22,260
You're confusing ginger
the actress

323
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:23,728
with ginger the character.

324
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:24,796
- Okay, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

325
00:14:24,798 --> 00:14:26,731
I'm totally getting, like,
a weird vibe from you right now.

326
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:28,366
It's like, a minute ago,
when we were shooting,

327
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,835
you were into me,
but now you're not.

328
00:14:30,837 --> 00:14:33,805
- That's because
ginger loves nuktuk,

329
00:14:33,807 --> 00:14:34,739
not bolin.

330
00:14:34,741 --> 00:14:36,841
- But nuktuk <i>is</i> bolin.

331
00:14:36,843 --> 00:14:39,277
I'm a hero.
[Sighs]

332
00:14:39,279 --> 00:14:44,082
- And that's why they call me
two toed ping.

333
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:47,986
- Because you have
two extra toes.

334
00:14:47,988 --> 00:14:48,786
- That's right.

335
00:14:48,788 --> 00:14:50,722
And there was already
a twelve toed ping

336
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:52,123
on the South side.

337
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:54,659
- Wait, guys.
Do you hear that?

338
00:14:54,661 --> 00:14:55,693
- I didn't hear anything.

339
00:14:55,695 --> 00:14:58,529
- No.
- Ah! What's taking so long?

340
00:14:58,531 --> 00:15:00,899
- You just gotta relax,
like me.

341
00:15:00,901 --> 00:15:02,634
Maybe try taking
your shoes off.

342
00:15:02,636 --> 00:15:04,068
- I'm gonna check it out.

343
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:07,705
- So how long do we have
to stay out here?

344
00:15:07,707 --> 00:15:11,142
- I told you,
it's gonna be a few hours.

345
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:12,944
What, do you have
a hot date?

346
00:15:12,946 --> 00:15:15,179
- Actually, I do.
And I wanna look my best.

347
00:15:15,181 --> 00:15:18,917
I gotta shower and shave.
I have a whole routine, okay?

348
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,852
- Well, your date's
gonna have to wait.

349
00:15:20,854 --> 00:15:23,521
- She's not gonna be happy
about that.

350
00:15:23,523 --> 00:15:24,122
- Too bad.

351
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:26,925
We were paid to keep mako
and that dame distracted

352
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:30,228
for a few hours,
so that's what we're gonna do.

353
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:34,365
- See, this is why
I never get dates.

354
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:48,980
- I just overheard
shady shin and viper.

355
00:15:48,982 --> 00:15:50,581
We've been double-crossed.

356
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:53,885
We have to get off
this ship.

357
00:15:54,219 --> 00:15:57,021
- Where do you think
you're going?

358
00:15:57,023 --> 00:15:59,290
- [Grunts]

359
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:05,129
- Get 'em!

360
00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:26,017
- [Shouts]

361
00:16:29,054 --> 00:16:31,422
- [Grunts]

362
00:16:43,569 --> 00:16:47,205
- [Screams]

363
00:16:47,207 --> 00:16:48,172
- Aah!

364
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:51,642
[Dramatic music]

365
00:16:51,644 --> 00:17:00,218
♪

366
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:01,986
They're getting closer.

367
00:17:01,988 --> 00:17:02,820
- Not for long.

368
00:17:02,822 --> 00:17:04,756
[Ship horn blares]
- Watch out!

369
00:17:04,758 --> 00:17:07,792
We're not gonna make it.

370
00:17:07,794 --> 00:17:10,895
All: Aah!

371
00:17:12,498 --> 00:17:14,599
- One down, one to go.

372
00:17:14,601 --> 00:17:16,167
Both: Oh!

373
00:17:16,169 --> 00:17:18,903
[Engine stalls]

374
00:17:20,773 --> 00:17:23,741
[Engine sputters]

375
00:17:23,743 --> 00:17:26,577
- We're stalled.

376
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,883
- [Grunts]

377
00:17:37,089 --> 00:17:39,223
- Unh!

378
00:17:43,162 --> 00:17:44,962
- Uhh! Ooh!

379
00:17:44,964 --> 00:17:46,564
[Engine starts]

380
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:49,567
- Mako, hang onto something.

381
00:17:49,569 --> 00:17:51,969
- Unh!

382
00:17:54,873 --> 00:17:55,640
- What was that all about?

383
00:17:55,642 --> 00:17:58,776
- Someone paid the triple
threats to keep us distracted.

384
00:17:58,778 --> 00:18:01,212
- Distracted?
From what?

385
00:18:01,214 --> 00:18:04,282
Oh, no.

386
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:18,429
- Whoever paid the triple
threats stole everything.

387
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:21,532
- I'm ruined.

388
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:27,472
- My company...
It's over.

389
00:18:27,474 --> 00:18:30,108
- We should check out
your other warehouses.

390
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,543
Maybe they didn't have time
to hit them all.

391
00:18:32,545 --> 00:18:34,145
- You don't understand.

392
00:18:34,147 --> 00:18:36,013
Everything I had
was in here.

393
00:18:36,015 --> 00:18:38,449
- We have to search the place
for evidence.

394
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:39,851
If we can find a lead...

395
00:18:39,853 --> 00:18:43,821
- Mako...
It doesn't matter anymore.

396
00:18:43,823 --> 00:18:45,289
- I can figure this out.

397
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:49,193
- Just stop.
It's over.

398
00:18:49,195 --> 00:18:50,394
I give up.

399
00:18:50,396 --> 00:18:56,267
- Well,
I'm not giving up on you.

400
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:02,874
[Gasps]

401
00:19:03,876 --> 00:19:05,543
- Sorry, I--

402
00:19:05,545 --> 00:19:09,347
- uh...It's--
it's okay.

403
00:19:09,349 --> 00:19:12,717
Um...Anyway...

404
00:19:12,719 --> 00:19:13,584
I gotta run.

405
00:19:13,586 --> 00:19:15,820
I'm gonna find out
who did this.

406
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:18,589
And I know just
who to ask.

407
00:19:20,125 --> 00:19:21,058
- Hey, mako.

408
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:23,761
Uh, you're not mad
about last night, are you?

409
00:19:23,763 --> 00:19:25,530
- Who hired you
to double-cross us?

410
00:19:25,532 --> 00:19:28,432
- I don't know.
- I think you do know.

411
00:19:28,434 --> 00:19:29,300
And you're gonna tell me,

412
00:19:29,302 --> 00:19:31,169
or we're gonna have
to change your name

413
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:32,136
to "no toed ping."

414
00:19:32,138 --> 00:19:35,273
- Really, I don't know.
You have to believe me.

415
00:19:35,275 --> 00:19:36,741
We never met the guy
who hired us.

416
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:39,744
- [Chuckles]
You expect me to believe that?

417
00:19:39,746 --> 00:19:41,679
- After you left the hideout,
some mook showed up

418
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:43,781
and said his boss would pay us
to keep you distracted.

419
00:19:43,783 --> 00:19:46,217
We'd never seen him before,
and we ain't seen him since.

420
00:19:46,219 --> 00:19:48,519
Come on, mako,
you know how these deals work.

421
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:49,687
Please.
I would never lie to you

422
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:52,924
with my lucky toes
on the line.

423
00:19:52,926 --> 00:19:55,059
- Get out of here.

424
00:19:55,061 --> 00:19:57,962
- [Panting]

425
00:20:00,432 --> 00:20:05,236
- Bolin, have you seen
varrick around?

426
00:20:05,238 --> 00:20:08,306
Bolin!

427
00:20:08,308 --> 00:20:10,174
[Sighs]

428
00:20:10,176 --> 00:20:12,076
Nuktuk.

429
00:20:12,078 --> 00:20:15,012
- Yes?
Oh, hello, mako.

430
00:20:15,014 --> 00:20:16,647
Didn't notice you there.

431
00:20:16,649 --> 00:20:18,382
- [Sighs]
Where's varrick?

432
00:20:18,384 --> 00:20:19,684
I need to ask him
something.

433
00:20:19,686 --> 00:20:21,919
- Hmm. Can't say
that I've seen him.

434
00:20:21,921 --> 00:20:23,554
But I've been kinda busy,
you know,

435
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:24,689
rehearsing for my big scene.

436
00:20:24,691 --> 00:20:27,992
There's gonna be
some crazy "pyrotechnics."

437
00:20:27,994 --> 00:20:29,860
That's mover speak
for explosions.

438
00:20:29,862 --> 00:20:33,231
- We need nuktuk on set.
Running explosion scene.

439
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:35,199
- Or sometimes we just
call them explosions.

440
00:20:35,201 --> 00:20:37,301
Anyway, wish I could
stand around here and chitchat,

441
00:20:37,303 --> 00:20:40,338
but you know, I gotta go
shoot my big scene.

442
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:41,772
[Bell rings]

443
00:20:41,774 --> 00:20:44,275
- Okay, the set is clear.

444
00:20:44,277 --> 00:20:45,443
Camera's rolling.

445
00:20:45,445 --> 00:20:46,844
And...Action!

446
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:49,880
- Ginger, stay down!
I'm coming for you.

447
00:20:49,882 --> 00:20:52,550
[Running footsteps]

448
00:20:55,187 --> 00:20:58,756
[Explosions]

449
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:05,229
- How did you rig
those explosions

450
00:21:05,231 --> 00:21:07,131
to go off like that?
- Neat, huh?

451
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:09,433
It's a varrick industries
exclusive.

452
00:21:09,435 --> 00:21:10,768
Here, check it out.

453
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:14,205
The explosions use
a remote detonator.

454
00:21:14,207 --> 00:21:16,040
- Varrick.

455
00:21:18,644 --> 00:21:22,213
Asami, I think I know
who set us up.

456
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:28,819
- Hello, mako.

457
00:21:28,821 --> 00:21:30,187
- What are you doing here?

458
00:21:30,189 --> 00:21:31,522
- He just saved
my company.

459
00:21:31,524 --> 00:21:35,359
Varrick bought a controlling
interest in future industries.

460
00:21:35,361 --> 00:21:37,161
Isn't that great?

461
00:21:37,163 --> 00:21:39,230
- Yep, I like to think
I'm always there

462
00:21:39,232 --> 00:21:40,464
to stand up
for the little guy.

463
00:21:40,466 --> 00:21:44,035
Especially if that little guy
can help this guy

464
00:21:44,037 --> 00:21:45,269
become a bigger guy.

465
00:21:45,271 --> 00:21:47,238
- So what were you saying,
mako?

466
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,607
You think you know
who hired the triple threats?

467
00:21:49,609 --> 00:21:54,512
- Yeah, and I'm real close
to proving it.

468
00:21:54,514 --> 00:21:59,216
I'll fill you in later.

469
00:22:12,898 --> 00:22:17,068
[Footsteps]

470
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:21,339
- [Grunts]

471
00:22:23,108 --> 00:22:24,675
[Gasps]

472
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:26,210
Get away from me!

473
00:22:26,212 --> 00:22:27,111
[Exhausted groans]

474
00:22:27,113 --> 00:22:31,115
- It's okay, we're here
to help you, avatar korra.

475
00:22:31,117 --> 00:22:33,417
- Who's--

476
00:22:33,419 --> 00:22:36,020
who's avatar korra?

477
00:22:40,158 --> 00:22:41,225
- What happened to you?

478
00:22:41,227 --> 00:22:43,627
How did you end up
on our island?

479
00:22:43,629 --> 00:22:47,264
- I...Don't know.

480
00:22:47,266 --> 00:22:49,900
I can't remember anything.

481
00:22:49,902 --> 00:22:50,935
[Sighs]

482
00:22:50,937 --> 00:22:53,337
[Groans]